INSERT INTO `page_parts` VALUES (1,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"gord-cooke-text\">\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" width=\"100%\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>\r\n            <h1>WELCOME</h1>\r\n            <p>Welcome to my website that is dedicated to helping the building industry and trade contractors build, renovate and sell more efficient, comfortable, healthier and more durable homes. As a professional engineer, trainer, author and industry consultant for the last 25 years, I have had the pleasure of working with great building professionals across North America who are dedicated to a path of continual improvement. <strong><a href=\"/profile\">Read more</a></strong> <img height=\"7\" width=\"8\" src=\"/images/arrow-white.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td width=\"201\"><img height=\"265\" width=\"201\" src=\"/images/gord-cooke.png\" alt=\"\" /></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"container_home\">\r\n<div><img height=\"235\" width=\"20\" src=\"/images/spacer.gif\" alt=\"\" /></div>\r\n<div id=\"homebox\">\r\n<div id=\"homebox1\"><img height=\"39\" width=\"259\" src=\"/images/titles/home_cookereport.png\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<p>Gord Cooke offers comprehensive seminar and workshop-based training programs to help his clients learn to build and sell better homes. These programs range from a systems approach to building better homes to marketing and selling the key features and benefits of those homes once a company has achieved a high standard of building performance. <span class=\"readmore\"><a href=\"/cooke-report\">Read more</a></span> <img height=\"7\" width=\"9\" src=\"/images/arrow-black.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<form action=\"\" method=\"post\" name=\"form\" id=\"form\">\r\n    <table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\">\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td colspan=\"2\">\r\n                <p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 3px;\" class=\"signup\">Sign-up for our Newsletter</p>\r\n                </td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td><input type=\"text\" style=\"width: 150px;\" value=\"EMAIL\" id=\"textfield\" name=\"textfield\" /></td>\r\n                <td><input type=\"image\" src=\"/images/b_submit.gif\" value=\"Submit\" id=\"button\" name=\"button\" /></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n</form>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"homebox2\">\r\n<div class=\"small-side-box\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px;\"><img height=\"19\" width=\"151\" src=\"/images/titles/home_upcomming-events.png\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<p>EEBA Board Meetings. <span class=\"readmore\"><a href=\"/events/events-calendar\">Read more</a></span> <img height=\"7\" width=\"9\" src=\"/images/arrow-black.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Enbridge Condo Ventilation Seminar. <span class=\"readmore\"><a href=\"/events/events-calendar\">Read more</a></span> <img height=\"7\" width=\"9\" src=\"/images/arrow-black.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"small-side-box\">\r\n<div style=\"padding: 9px 12px;\"><img height=\"16\" width=\"111\" src=\"/images/titles/home_in-the-media.png\" alt=\"\" /><br />\r\n<p>Green Building Requirements.. <span class=\"readmore\"><a href=\"/pdf/CondoBusiness%20April%202009.pdf\">Read more</a></span> <img height=\"7\" width=\"9\" src=\"/images/arrow-black.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Stay informed on all of the newsworthy activities. <span class=\"readmore\"><a href=\"/media-room/in-the-news/\">Read more</a></span> <img height=\"7\" width=\"9\" src=\"/images/arrow-black.png\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>',1),(2,'extended','','',1),(3,'body','','',2),(4,'extended','','',2),(5,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/in-the-news.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />IN THE NEWS</h1>\r\n<p>Stay informed on all of the newsworthy activities associated with Gord Cooke and his team of industry-leading building experts and educators. These professionals are in-demand and constantly innovating, so there will always be something new for you to discover here. Check back often.</p>\r\n<p>[Will include content from all public relations efforts, provided by GSL]</p>\r\n</div>',3),(6,'extended','','',3),(7,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/articles-publications.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />ARTICLES &amp; PUBLICATIONS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke is a regular contributor to a variety of industry publications and writes a monthly column on indoor air quality for HPAC magazine. To access these informative, easy-to-read articles, simply click on the links below.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mechanical Business Magazine Articles        </strong></p>\r\n<p>Tackling HVAC Leakage: Tight Design is Good Design         <a href=\"http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/december_2008\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/december_2008</a></p>\r\n<p>Tools for the High Performance HVAC Trade         <a href=\"http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/september_2008\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/september_2008</a></p>\r\n<p>High Performance HVAC: Things that don&rsquo;t work, and some that do         <a href=\"http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/july_2008\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/july_2008</a></p>\r\n<p>Taking A/C on the Green Road to Performance<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/may_2008\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/may_2008</a></p>\r\n<p>Turning Buildings Green<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/april_2008\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.mechanicalbusiness.com/archives/april_2008</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>HPAC Magazine Articles</strong></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Working out HVAC Design Details         <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=278\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=278</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Hot Time to Sell Efficiency<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=10\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=10</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Ventilation Makes the Grade         <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=363\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=363</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Shades of Green<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=329\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=329</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Creating Conduits Conducive to Efficiency and Health<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=303\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=303</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Ventilation as a Principle Strategy (Part 1)<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=105\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=105 </a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Facts and Stats         <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=464\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=464</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Working Out: HVAC Design Details in Fitness Centres         <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=278\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=278</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Mitigating Risk: Reducing Air Leakage         <br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=422\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=422</a></p>\r\n<p>IAQ - Old Homes: Presenting the Case for Mechanical Ventilation Systems<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=211\" target=\"_blank\">http://hpac.sartech.ca/digimag/display.asp?a=211 </a></p>\r\n</div>',4),(8,'extended','','',4),(9,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/helpful-links.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />HELPFUL LINKS</h1>\r\n<p>These links have been compiled to provide you with additional resources related to the building industry and better building practices.</p>\r\n<p>PEO: Professional Engineers of Ontario<br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.peo.on.ca\">http://www.peo.on.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>HRAI: Heating Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Institute of Canada<br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hrai.ca\">http://www.hrai.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>OHBA: Ontario Home Builders Association         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.homesontario.com\">http://www.homesontario.com</a></p>\r\n<p>CHBA: Canadian Home Builders Association         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.chba.ca\">http://www.chba.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>CaGBC: Canadian Green Building Council         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cagbc.org\">http://www.cagbc.org</a></p>\r\n<p>HPBAC: Hearth Patio BBQ Association of Canada         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hpbacanada.org\">http://www.hpbacanada.org</a></p>\r\n<p>OHAO: Occupational Hygiene Association of Ontario         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ohao.org\">http://www.ohao.org</a></p>\r\n<p>CSA: Canadian Standards Association<br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.csa.ca\">http://www.csa.ca </a></p>\r\n<p>CMHC: Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp., International Housing Technology Transfer Team         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cmhc-schl.gc.ca/en\">http://www.cmhc-schl.gc.ca/en</a></p>\r\n<p>CRESNET: Canadian Residential Energy Services Network         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://cresnet.ca\">http://cresnet.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>EEBA: Energy and Environmental Building Association, Board Member         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eeba.org\">http://www.eeba.org</a></p>\r\n<p>CPSA: Canadian Professional Sales Association         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cpsa.com\">http://www.cpsa.com</a></p>\r\n<p>Environment Canada<br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ec.gc.ca\">http://www.ec.gc.ca</a></p>\r\n<p>U.S. Environmental Protection Agency         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.epa.gov\">http://www.epa.gov</a></p>\r\n<p>Canadian Lung Association<br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"www.lung.ca\">www.lung.ca </a></p>\r\n<p>Health and Energy         <br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://healthandenergy.com\">http://healthandenergy.com</a></p>\r\n</div>',5),(10,'extended','','',5),(11,'body','','',6),(12,'extended','','',6),(13,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />BIOGRAPHY</h1>\r\n<p>Welcome to my website that is dedicated to helping the building industry and trade contractors build, renovate and sell more efficient, comfortable, healthier and more durable homes. As a professional engineer, trainer, author and industry consultant for the last 25 years, I have had the pleasure of working with great building professionals across North America who are dedicated to a path of continual improvement.</p>\r\n<p>As in all the training I do, I welcome your comments, feedback and interaction. We are a large and diverse industry &ndash; manufacturers, designers, consultants, suppliers, trade contractors, sales agents, building officials, energy raters, government representatives, builders and renovators. All of us have an important viewpoint on the industry, so please engage in the betterment of our industry by using and responding to the information presented.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you: Gord Cooke</p>\r\n<p><strong>Biography       </strong></p>\r\n<p>For the past two decades, Gord Cooke has been an effective and passionate educator and advocate for better building practices, improved indoor air quality and energy efficiency. He has a unique talent of taking the complex issues of building science and breaking them into easily understood elements with practical real-world applications for all audiences.       Gord&rsquo;s building science training curricula covers the gamut from creating and delivering basic and advanced building science principles through managing indoor air quality to HVAC system design to an intensive sales training workshop. He has pioneered new training programs designed to assist builders in the sales and marketing of higher performing, energy efficient homes -- helping builders more effectively tell their story to customers, increase their margins and sell more homes.</p>\r\n<p>Gord has delivered sessions at such conferences as the NAHB&rsquo;s International Builders Show, Energy Design Conference, JLC Live, West Coast Green and the National Green Building Conference and is an active Energy &amp; Environmental Building Association (EEBA) board member and certified trainer. He authored the Build Comfort Program and provided instruction for both the Union and Enbridge Gas companies. Additionally, Gord has authored and co-authored numerous white papers and research studies related to indoor air quality and home performance issues, contributes a monthly IAQ column to HPAC magazine and is a certified R-2000 Design Evaluator and Trainer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recent Training and Project Experience        </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>National Trainer, CMHC&rsquo;s Let&rsquo;s Clear The Air Workshop, Build and Renovate to Avoid Mold, and The 3-Day IAQ Investigators Workshop, Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp.</li>\r\n    <li>Author and Trainer, Introduction of Natural Gas Technical Training, Irving Oil Ltd.</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Author, Air Tightness of Houses and Their Duct Systems Study, Consumers Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Quality Assurance Inspector, EnerGuide For Houses Program, Natural Resources Canada</li>\r\n    <li>Author and Trainer, Technical Sales Workshop for New Home Sales Agents, EnerQuality Corp. and NRCan</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Author and Certified Trainer, Domestic Energy Advisor 5 Day Accredited Course, Seneca College</li>\r\n    <li>Certified Trainer, Houses That Work  - Building Science Workshop, EEBA</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, House as a System Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Trainer, Building Science Workshop for Mechanical Contractors, Union Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Trainer, Ontario Green Communities Initiative, in co-operation with the Energy Training Centre of Seneca College</li>\r\n    <li>Team Member, Build Canada Initiative,  EnerQuality Corporation</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, Tankless Water Heater Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, HE Furnace Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, Technical Training Program for Energy Management Consultants, Direct Energy</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Developer and Trainer, First Nations Indoor Air Quality Workshop Series, in co-operation with Turtle Island, CMHC</li>\r\n    <li>National Technical Trainer and Advisor, Broan &ndash; Nutone - Venmar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',7),(14,'extended','','',7),(15,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />MISSION &amp; VALUES</h1>\r\n<p>Gord&rsquo;s mission is to help improve the quality, comfort, durability and energy efficiency of new homes in Ontario and North America through education and innovative products.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<p>To provide technical representation of innovative energy efficient products to the building industry.         <br />\r\nTo provide products for the improvement of indoor air quality.<br />\r\nTo provide services and support to builders to help improve building practices and meet and exceed building program guidelines.<br />\r\nTo provide technical and sales &amp; marketing training to the housing market and related building industries to lessen the impact of building on the environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Values</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gord VALUES :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The outdoor and indoor living environments. All of the products and services he provides are aimed at lessening the environmental footprint of building houses without compromising health or comfort.</li>\r\n    <li>His business relationships. Gord endeavours to build long term relationships with his clients, based on honesty, trust, good service and mutual respect.</li>\r\n    <li>His staff and associates. Gord strives to strengthen their individual understanding and knowledge base by encouraging professional development, and by providing strong leadership and mentoring to maintain the integrity of his company.</li>\r\n    <li>His reputation. Gord takes pride in being a leader in new building technologies, being easy to work with and for, and in being a first call resource for his clients.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',8),(16,'extended','','',8),(17,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />EXPERTISE &amp; EXPERIENCE</h1>\r\n<p>Gord has a wide range of expertise and experience that allows him to appreciate and respond to a wide range of clients and their issues :</p>\r\n<p><strong>Technical Expertise </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>His formal background in the industry started with ventilation and HVAC systems in both residential and institutional buildings. That led him to the study of indoor air quality and he was the first person to complete the Canada Mortgage and Housing Indoor Air Quality Investigators program. He conducts audits in existing homes for homeowners with serious indoor air quality issues.</li>\r\n    <li>He now trains a variety of HVAC contractors, home inspectors and health officials on how to investigate complex IAQ issues in existing homes in a practical way.</li>\r\n    <li>He has been conducting energy audits and performance testing new homes under the R-2000 and ENERGY STAR for New Homes program for over 20 years, working with large volume and custom builders to identify the most practical solutions for improving energy efficiency and durability.</li>\r\n    <li>As a young engineer, he helped design innovative ventilation products for schools and homes and more recently has helped government agencies and manufacturers evaluate new innovative technologies for the building industry &ndash; including HVAC systems, solar, water heating options and insulation products.</li>\r\n    <li>Gord is an active Building Canada team member, helping large volume builders find cost effective solutions to improving energy efficiency</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Sales Experience :        </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Gord has run a successful sales agency since 1986, always concentrating on developing and growing new markets for innovative building industry products.</li>\r\n    <li>He relates this valuable experience when training HVAC contractors, window sales agents and especially new home sales agents on the essential sales process elements for high performance new homes and products.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Program Development :            </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Gord became the interim manager of the Ontario R-2000 program, Canada&rsquo;s leading housing energy efficiency program, in the early 1990&rsquo;s. His experience with leading builders as their energy evaluator helped the program focus on the key elements of a new home energy efficiency program.</li>\r\n    <li>Gord was also the co-author of a college diploma course on building science. He worked with the college to develop both an in-house program for young students and an out-reach program for industry clients.</li>\r\n    <li>Since that time, he has consulted with utilities, government agencies and Standards writing committees to help them implement new programs and standards to the building industry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This wide circle of experience allows Gord to appreciate the needs of the widest possible range of clients in the building industry &ndash; from manufacturers to homeowners, building officials to trade contractors, utilities to educational institutions. It is Gord&rsquo;s unique ability to take complex issues and view them from many focal points, always with an eye to finding practical and cost effective solutions, that is of such great value to clients.</p>\r\n</div>',9),(18,'extended','','',9),(19,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />MEMBERSHIPS &amp; AWARDS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord has achieved a high standard of recognition and respect from his peers in the building industry over the last 20 years. Here is a list of his industry association memberships and some awards he has received.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Memberships :             </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>PEO - </strong>Professional Engineers of Ontario<br />\r\n<strong>HRAI</strong> - Heating Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Institute of Canada              <br />\r\n<strong>OHBA</strong> - 	Ontario Home Builders Association              <br />\r\n<strong>CHBA</strong> - Canadian Home Builders Association              <br />\r\n<strong>CaGBC</strong> - Canadian Green Building Council              <br />\r\n<strong>HPBAC</strong> - Hearth Patio BBQ Association of Canada              <br />\r\n<strong>OHAO</strong> - Occupational Hygiene Association of Ontario              <br />\r\n<strong>CSA</strong> - Canadian Standards Association, Technical Committee for Heating Ventilation Air            Conditioning and Refrigeration              Previous Chairman of the CSA F326 Residential Mechanical Ventilation Sub Committee              <br />\r\n<strong>CMHC</strong> - Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp., International Housing Technology Transfer Team              <br />\r\n<strong>CRESNET</strong> - Canadian Residential Energy Services Network              <br />\r\n<strong>EEBA</strong> - Energy and Environmental Building Association, Board Member              <br />\r\n<strong>CPSA</strong> - Canadian Professional Sales Association</p>\r\n<p><strong>Awards :             </strong></p>\r\n<p>EnerQuality Corp./ OHBA  &ndash; Hall of Fame Inductee 2007              <br />\r\nEnergy Evaluator of the Year<br />\r\nR-2000 Evaluator of the Year</p>\r\n</div>',10),(20,'extended','','',10),(21,'body','Fckeditor','',11),(22,'extended','','',11),(23,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-children\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />SERVICES OFFERED</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke offers comprehensive consulting services to help builders, architects and remodelers continuously improve their practices to deliver high performance homes. Gord provides support from the smallest first steps to a complete change in design and construction practices. He helps you fix problems as they arise and, most importantly, before they happen.</p>\r\n<p>He has helped hundreds of clients achieve the goals of building programs such as LEED for Homes, ENERGY STAR for New Homes, American Lung Association&rsquo;s Health House Program, and others.</p>\r\n<h1>SITE ASSESSMENTS AND WORKSHOPS</h1>\r\n<p>As an essential complement to his training services, Gord Cooke offers interactive, on-site workshops focused on identifying key design and construction issues and creating solutions. These workshops are critical to building better homes as they provide the opportunity to bring together diverse stakeholders (site supervisors, sales staff, construction trades, etc.) to discuss key issues and challenges, and provide a forum for identifying and solving problems.</p>\r\n<p>Workshops combine training seminars with construction site walk-throughs. A follow-up report outlines observations made on site, including problem areas, best practices, and a planning timeline for implementing changes.</p>\r\n<h1>PERFORMANCE EVALUATION &amp; RECOMMENDATIONS</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Assessments       </strong></p>\r\n<p>Design and construction assessments are one of the most important beginning steps to building better homes. Gord Cooke provides expert design and construction reviews to assist his clients in developing a clear picture of current practices, short and long term goals, and a roadmap to achieve these goals.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recommendations</strong></p>\r\n<p>A home is not complete unless Gord Cooke and his team ensure that it&rsquo;s performing to the standard to which it was designed. Gord provides coordination of testing and diagnostic services and recommendations in order to provide an essential feedback loop on the end performance of each home. His role is to help you develop a good test plan, make sure it&rsquo;s being implemented appropriately and help you understand and act on test results.</p>\r\n<h1>PLAN &amp; SPECIFICATIONS REVIEW</h1>\r\n<p>An average home consists of 15,000 building components that are put together by over 200 different people from 14 different trades. But a home is much more than an assembly of parts. A home is an interactive system and each of its components must be designed to work together. During a plan review, Gord analyzes the following components with the &ldquo;Systems Approach&rdquo; in mind :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Foundations</li>\r\n    <li>Water Management Details</li>\r\n    <li>Walls</li>\r\n    <li>Roofs</li>\r\n    <li>Insulation</li>\r\n    <li>Air Sealing</li>\r\n    <li>HVAC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Extensive system review, material recommendations and design assistance (followed by proper installation) ensure that each home operates as efficiently and effectively as possible.</p>\r\n<h1>INDOOR AIR QUALITY AUDITS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke and his team were among the first in Canada to complete the Canada Mortgage and Housing Indoor Air Quality Auditors training and apprenticeship program.</p>\r\n<p>This in-home investigation service, offered to homeowners in Southern Ontario, is a comprehensive investigation with a full, written report identifying opportunities for improving air quality and ensuring homeowners are breathing the best possible air in the home. The process focuses on identifying solutions that are practical and affordable. Audit services are also available for small commercial buildings so employees can enjoy a healthier environment.</p>\r\n<h1>SPECIALIZED AIR QUALITY TESTING</h1>\r\n<p>Some air quality problems are the result of complex and often hidden problems. In these cases, Gord Cooke offers, in cooperation with certified laboratories :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Mold Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Volatile Organic Compound Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Combustion Products Analysis</li>\r\n    <li>Particulate Matter Identification</li>\r\n    <li>Material Testing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>AIR TIGHTNESS TESTING</h1>\r\n<p>Unwanted air leakage in and out of houses and buildings is responsible for as much as 40% of the heating bill for most homeowners. In addition, many comfort problems, building failures and mold concerns are related to air leakage. Gord Cooke has both the specialized equipment and expertise to test and solve air leakage problems in houses, duct systems and small commercial buildings in Southern Ontario.</p>\r\n<h1>ENERGY AUDITS AND SIMULATIONS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke has 15 years of experience in performance testing, energy auditing and energy simulation of houses and small commercial buildings. He is a certified R-2000 design evaluator, air tightness tester and inspector, an EnerGuide for Houses Quality Assurance contractor and an ENERGY STAR contractor. He can help builders, renovators and homeowners optimize energy use in new and existing homes.</p>\r\n<p>For more information on how Gord Cooke and his team can help you develop a manageable plan of action to increase the quality and performance of your homes, <a href=\"mailto:info@gordcook.com\">click here</a>.</p>\r\n<h1>INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC BENEFITS / BUILDERS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Sales training on how to effectively educate and sell high performance features and benefits to home buyers</li>\r\n    <li>Energy rating for programs such as ENERGY STAR for New Homes, LEED for Homes, GreenHouse and Built Green</li>\r\n    <li>Air quality evaluation &ndash; specifically assessing clean up requirements for mold</li>\r\n    <li>Heating, cooling and ventilation system design</li>\r\n    <li>Consultation on finding cost effective ideas for improving durability and energy efficiency</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with developing marketing messages for high performance homes</li>\r\n    <li>Resolving building code issues</li>\r\n    <li>Technical training of site staff and trades on high performance products and techniques</li>\r\n    <li>Benchmarking current construction practices and developing a plan for technical improvement.</li>\r\n    <li>Trouble-shooting and complaints resolution with complex building science issues and product performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC BENEFITS / MANUFACTURERS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of sales people on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry &ndash; developing a sales process that works well in the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials to enable new product introduction</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC BENEFITS / UTILITIES &amp; GOVERNMENT AGENCIES</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of industry representatives on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials, government agencies to assist in the introduction of programs and products</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages and program elements to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC BENEFITS / SUPPLIERS &amp; TRADE CONTRACTORS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of sales people on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry &ndash; developing a sales process that works well in the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Technical training for design and installation of new products</li>\r\n    <li>Trouble-shooting and complaints resolution with complex building science issues and product performance.</li>\r\n    <li>Education and training on adapting to new industry programs, products and techniques.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC BENEFITS / ASSOCIATIONS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Assistance with new program development that best matches with industry needs</li>\r\n    <li>Training of industry representatives on behalf of associations &ndash; both sales and technical</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials, government agencies to assist in the introduction of programs and products</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages and program elements to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',12),(24,'extended','','',12),(25,'body','','',13),(26,'extended','','',13),(27,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" /> SITE ASSESSMENTS AND WORKSHOPS</h1>\r\n<p>As an essential complement to his training services, Gord Cooke offers interactive, on-site workshops focused on identifying key design and construction issues and creating solutions. These workshops are critical to building better homes as they provide the opportunity to bring together diverse stakeholders (site supervisors, sales staff, construction trades, etc.) to discuss key issues and challenges, and provide a forum for identifying and solving problems.</p>\r\n<p>Workshops combine training seminars with construction site walk-throughs. A follow-up report outlines observations made on site, including problem areas, best practices, and a planning timeline for implementing changes.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',14),(28,'extended','','',14),(29,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />PERFORMANCE EVALUATION &amp; RECOMMENDATIONS</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Assessments       </strong></p>\r\n<p>Design and construction assessments are one of the most important beginning steps to building better homes. Gord Cooke provides expert design and construction reviews to assist his clients in developing a clear picture of current practices, short and long term goals, and a roadmap to achieve these goals.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recommendations</strong></p>\r\n<p>A home is not complete unless Gord Cooke and his team ensure that it&rsquo;s performing to the standard to which it was designed. Gord provides coordination of testing and diagnostic services and recommendations in order to provide an essential feedback loop on the end performance of each home. His role is to help you develop a good test plan, make sure it&rsquo;s being implemented appropriately and help you understand and act on test results.</p>\r\n</div>',15),(30,'extended','','',15),(31,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />PLAN &amp; SPECIFICATIONS REVIEW</h1>\r\n<p>An average home consists of 15,000 building components that are put together by over 200 different people from 14 different trades. But a home is much more than an assembly of parts. A home is an interactive system and each of its components must be designed to work together. During a plan review, Gord analyzes the following components with the &ldquo;Systems Approach&rdquo; in mind :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Foundations</li>\r\n    <li>Water Management Details</li>\r\n    <li>Walls</li>\r\n    <li>Roofs</li>\r\n    <li>Insulation</li>\r\n    <li>Air Sealing</li>\r\n    <li>HVAC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Extensive system review, material recommendations and design assistance (followed by proper installation) ensure that each home operates as efficiently and effectively as possible.</p>\r\n</div>',16),(32,'extended','','',16),(33,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />INDOOR AIR QUALITY AUDITS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke and his team were among the first in Canada to complete the Canada Mortgage and Housing Indoor Air Quality Auditors training and apprenticeship program.</p>\r\n<p>This in-home investigation service, offered to homeowners in Southern Ontario, is a comprehensive investigation with a full, written report identifying opportunities for improving air quality and ensuring homeowners are breathing the best possible air in the home. The process focuses on identifying solutions that are practical and affordable. Audit services are also available for small commercial buildings so employees can enjoy a healthier environment.</p>\r\n</div>',17),(34,'extended','','',17),(35,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />SPECIALIZED AIR QUALITY TESTING</h1>\r\n<p>Some air quality problems are the result of complex and often hidden problems. In these cases, Gord Cooke offers, in cooperation with certified laboratories :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Mold Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Volatile Organic Compound Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Combustion Products Analysis</li>\r\n    <li>Particulate Matter Identification</li>\r\n    <li>Material Testing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>',18),(36,'extended','','',18),(37,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />AIR TIGHTNESS TESTING</h1>\r\n<p>Unwanted air leakage in and out of houses and buildings is responsible for as much as 40% of the heating bill for most homeowners. In addition, many comfort problems, building failures and mold concerns are related to air leakage. Gord Cooke has both the specialized equipment and expertise to test and solve air leakage problems in houses, duct systems and small commercial buildings in Southern Ontario.</p>\r\n</div>',19),(38,'extended','','',19),(39,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />ENERGY AUDITS AND SIMULATIONS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke has 15 years of experience in performance testing, energy auditing and energy simulation of houses and small commercial buildings. He is a certified R-2000 design evaluator, air tightness tester and inspector, an EnerGuide for Houses Quality Assurance contractor and an ENERGY STAR contractor. He can help builders, renovators and homeowners optimize energy use in new and existing homes.</p>\r\n<p>For more information on how Gord Cooke and his team can help you develop a manageable plan of action to increase the quality and performance of your homes, <a href=\"mailto:info@gordcook.com\">click here</a>.</p>\r\n</div>',20),(40,'extended','','',20),(41,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/cooke-report.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />TRAINING WORKSHOPS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke offers comprehensive seminar and workshop-based training programs to help his clients learn to build and sell better homes. These programs range from a systems approach to building better homes to marketing and selling the key features and benefits of those homes once a company has achieved a high standard of building performance.</p>\r\n<p>These workshops and seminars are designed for anyone in the construction industry. Clients include home builders, as well as home builder&rsquo;s associations, manufacturers, architects and utilities who wish to provide training as a value added service to their customers.</p>\r\n<p>These customized training programs include :</p>\r\n<p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.buildingknowledge.com/training/CompBS.pdf\">Comprehensive Building Science Training</a><br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.buildingknowledge.com/training/UnderstandingGreen.pdf\">Do You Want that in Green?</a><br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.buildingknowledge.com/training/MktgandSelling.pdf\">Marketing and Selling the Better Built Home</a><br />\r\n<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.buildingknowledge.com/training/MoistureRainMgmt.pdf\">Moisture and Rain Management </a></p>\r\n<h1>SPONSORS</h1>\r\n<p>Gord&rsquo;s training programs are sponsored by a wide variety of building industry companies, organizations and associations. Consider working with your local association, HBA, utility, lumber yard or product distributor to sponsor a training program in your area. Please contact us to learn more.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Gord Cooke Training Program Sponsors</strong></p>\r\n<p>Primary Sponsors<br />\r\nTO COME<br />\r\n[insert logos that link to each sponsor&rsquo;s website] TO COME</p>\r\n<p>Secondary Sponsors         <br />\r\nTO COME<br />\r\n[insert logos that link to each sponsor&rsquo;s website] TO COME</p>\r\n</div>',21),(42,'extended','','',21),(43,'body','Fckeditor','',22),(44,'extended','','',22),(45,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/contact.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1>CONTACT US</h1>\r\n<p>Do you have questions, comments or require additional information?  If so, we encourage you to contact us.</p>\r\n<div id=\"contact_form-box\">\r\n<div id=\"theform\">\r\n<form action=\"\" method=\"post\" name=\"form\" id=\"form\">\r\n    <p><label>Name:</label><br />\r\n    <input type=\"text\" style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 170px;\" id=\"textfield\" name=\"textfield\" /></p>\r\n    <p><label>Email:</label><br />\r\n    <input type=\"text\" style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 170px;\" id=\"textfield2\" name=\"textfield2\" /></p>\r\n    <p><label>Comments:</label><br />\r\n    <textarea style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 320px;\" id=\"textfield3\" rows=\"5\" name=\"textfield3\"></textarea></p>\r\n    <table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\">\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td width=\"25\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"checkbox\" name=\"checkbox\" /></td>\r\n                <td><span class=\"smalltxt\">Yes, I would like to receive information<br />\r\n                on upcomin events and company news. </span></td>\r\n                <td width=\"80\" style=\"padding-right: 20px;\"><input type=\"image\" src=\"/images/b_submit_inner.gif\" value=\"Submit\" id=\"button\" name=\"button\" /></td>\r\n            </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n</form>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"contact-info\">\r\n<h2>GORD COOKE</h2>\r\n<p>Building Technologies<br />\r\n<br />\r\n240 Holiday Inn Drive, Suite K,<br />\r\nCambridge, Ontario N3C 3X4<br />\r\n<br />\r\nT: 519 658 6232 / 800 267 6830<br />\r\nF: 519 658 6103<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"mailto:info@gordcooke.com\">info@gordcooke.com</a></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>',23),(46,'extended','','',23),(47,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/industry.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />ASSOCIATIONS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Assistance with new program development that best matches with industry needs</li>\r\n    <li>Training of industry representatives on behalf of associations &ndash; both sales and technical</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials, government agencies to assist in the introduction of programs and products</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages and program elements to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',24),(48,'extended','','',24),(49,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/industry.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />BUILDERS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Sales training on how to effectively educate and sell high performance features and benefits to home buyers</li>\r\n    <li>Energy rating for programs such as ENERGY STAR for New Homes, LEED for Homes, GreenHouse and Built Green</li>\r\n    <li>Air quality evaluation &ndash; specifically assessing clean up requirements for mold</li>\r\n    <li>Heating, cooling and ventilation system design</li>\r\n    <li>Consultation on finding cost effective ideas for improving durability and energy efficiency</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with developing marketing messages for high performance homes</li>\r\n    <li>Resolving building code issues</li>\r\n    <li>Technical training of site staff and trades on high performance products and techniques</li>\r\n    <li>Benchmarking current construction practices and developing a plan for technical improvement.</li>\r\n    <li>Trouble-shooting and complaints resolution with complex building science issues and product performance.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>',25),(50,'extended','','',25),(51,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/industry.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />MANUFACTURERS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of sales people on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry &ndash; developing a sales process that works well in the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials to enable new product introduction</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>',26),(52,'extended','','',26),(53,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/industry.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />UTILITIES &amp; GOVERNMENT AGENCIES</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of industry representatives on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Education and liaison with building code officials, government agencies to assist in the introduction of programs and products</li>\r\n    <li>Assistance with the development of marketing messages and program elements to the industry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',27),(54,'extended','','',27),(55,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/industry.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"sub-navigation-sibling\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />SUPPLIERS &amp; TRADE CONTRACTORS</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Helping evaluate and field testing new innovative building products</li>\r\n    <li>Training of sales people on how to approach and work at various levels within the building industry &ndash; developing a sales process that works well in the building industry</li>\r\n    <li>Technical training for design and installation of new products</li>\r\n    <li>Trouble-shooting and complaints resolution with complex building science issues and product performance.</li>\r\n    <li>Education and training on adapting to new industry programs, products and techniques.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',28),(56,'extended','','',28),(57,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/team.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1>TEAM</h1>\r\n<div><img width=\"132\" height=\"200\" align=\"left\" src=\"/images/team/rob-johnston.jpg\" style=\"margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p><strong>Rob Johnston &ndash;Builder Services Manager, Builder Liaison</strong></p>\r\n<p>After 20 years of hands-on experience in the custom machinery industry, Rob felt it was time for a career change. Combining his experience in renovating and homebuilding with his desire to develop and pursue new technologies, Rob quickly became an integral part of our company. For the last 6 years, his dedication, extensive knowledge and management background have been an invaluable part of growing our Builder Services team and division. Currently, Rob is focusing on his role of assisting builders (big and small) with the creation and implementation of their chosen energy programs. Whether it is ENERGY STAR, LEED for New Homes or GreenHouse, Rob is able to create cost effective option plans individualized to suit every builder. His dedication and knowledge are invaluable to both our company and the builders we service.</p>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><img width=\"132\" height=\"200\" align=\"left\" src=\"/images/team/angela-bustamante.jpg\" style=\"margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 0px;\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<p><strong>Angela Bustamante C.E.T &ndash; Energy Evaluator / Administrator, Builder Services        </strong></p>\r\n<p>The success of any good company rests on the dedication and knowledge of its employees and Angela, our Builder Services Administrator, is a great example. Her interest in drafting and homebuilding began at a young age. Her thirst for knowledge has led her to both an Environmental Engineering Diploma and a Construction Engineer Technologist Degree. Her experience and education is both multi-faceted and extensive; from working with a non-profit organization specializing in helping Canadian immigrant families with energy efficiency to IAQ training and thermographic camera analysis. As a liaison, Angela provides support and assistance to our home builders and various service providers. She is also actively involved in ventilation design, air testing and energy software simulations.</p>\r\n<div style=\"clear: both;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>ASSOCIATES</h1>\r\n<p>Gord is very proud to have worked with many outstanding consultants to the industry. It has always been his philosophy that collaboration leads to the most practical solutions to complex issues. Many of the projects that Gord works on include a team approach, each member with individual strengths, focus and experience. It is Gord&rsquo;s pleasure to introduce website visitors to important industry participants that Gord has been associated with.</p>\r\n<p>Mark - TO COME         <br />\r\nEd - TO COME         <br />\r\nPat - TO COME         <br />\r\nTex - TO COME         <br />\r\nGail - TO COME</p>\r\n</div>',29),(58,'extended','','',29),(59,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/services-offred.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />ASSOCIATES</h1>\r\n<p>Gord is very proud  to have worked with many outstanding consultants to the industry. It has always  been his philosophy that collaboration leads to the most practical solutions to  complex issues. Many of the projects that Gord works on include a team  approach, each member with individual strengths, focus and experience. It is  Gord&rsquo;s pleasure to introduce website visitors to important industry  participants that Gord has been associated with.</p>\r\n<p>Mark - TO COME<br />\r\nEd - TO COME<br />\r\nPat - TO COME<br />\r\nTex - TO COME<br />\r\nGail - TO COME</p>\r\n</div>',30),(60,'extended','','',30),(61,'body','Fckeditor','	<div id=\"header-inner\"><img src=\"/images/headers/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" height=\"96\" width=\"980\"></div>\r\n<r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\" />\r\n	<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n      <h1><img src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" align=\"right\" height=\"312\" width=\"169\">SUCCESS STORIES</h1>\r\n      <p>ON HOLD - REVISED CONTENT TO COME</p>\r\n</div>\r\n',31),(62,'extended','','',31),(63,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/testimonials.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"312\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />TESTIMONIALS</h1>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Gord is an excellent communicator. The use of various materials to encourage participant involvement assisted in [our] learning experience.&rdquo;         </em><br />\r\n<strong>Don Johnston, Senior Director, Canadian Home Builders Association </strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Gord is a people-friendly engineer that can provide a sales team both inspiration and knowledge, no matter how well-trained they are.&rdquo;         </em><br />\r\n<strong>Will Worth, President &amp; CEO, Medallion Homes, Texas</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Gord was [a] very informative and dynamic speaker. I heard nothing but complements. I believe everyone in attendance gained a great deal [of] knowledge on how to build better, more efficient housing.&rdquo; </em><br />\r\n<strong>Jenefer Russum, Planner DNREC DE Energy Office</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;The sales staff who attended Gord&rsquo;s session responded very well to the information, role playing and ideas which he presented and they have worked to continuously improve their skills. Our expectations were definitely exceeded and we will continue to raise the bar for our people and our company with Gord&rsquo;s training.&rdquo;</em><br />\r\n<strong>Rich Coyle, Purchasing Manager D R Horton, Sacramento, CA</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been to major seminars and conferences for 20 years, [Gord was the] best speaker I&rsquo;ve ever heard. [We] must have him back.&rdquo; </em><br />\r\n<strong>Building Science session attendee from St. Louis, MO in June 2006 </strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;We had almost 100 sales representatives, builders and developers from our network in attendance and their feedback on your presentation, both informal and through the conference evaluation forms, was universally positive. Your mastery of your material from both the technical and sales perspectives was clear, as always. Many asked that we bring you back again and, given that this is the third year in a row that you have presented to our group that is no small compliment. Thank you for helping us to stay on the leading edge.&rdquo;</em><br />\r\n<strong>David Poupore, President, Guildcrest Building Corporation, Ontario, Canada, March 2009</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;On behalf of the entire Energy Design Conference Team and the over 1,000 registrants who attended the conference, I want to thank you for presenting at the 2009 Energy Design Conference &amp; Expo. We received an abundance of positive comments regarding the scope, content, and quality of your sessions. It is your energy, knowledge, and passion for what you do that make this conference such an educational and exciting event for our attendees. The heart of this event is the content of the sessions&mdash;thank you for going above and beyond our expectations. Congratulations on a job well done!&rdquo;</em><br />\r\n<strong>Amanda Oja, Minnesota Power, Duluth, MN, March 2009 </strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I attend many seminars. I have never rated a seminar excellent all round before. Gord is interesting, right pace and polished. No long war stories or audience digressions.&rdquo;</em><br />\r\n<strong>Building Performance Contractors Association seminar attendee, NY State in April 2009 </strong></p>\r\n<p>The following are comments from attendees of the 2009 Better Building : Better Business Conference in Wisconsin, where Gord&rsquo;s seminar was ranked 4th out of 60 with 98% of respondents indicating that they would seek Gord out as a presenter :</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Very informative, practical &amp; humorous!&rdquo;                  <br />\r\n&ldquo;One of the best, most straightforward HVAC presentations I&rsquo;ve ever attended!&rdquo;                <br />\r\n&ldquo;Very knowledgeable presenter, very enthusiastic presenter.&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;An instructor that geared his class for HVAC contractors.  Thank you.&rdquo;                  <br />\r\n&ldquo;Gord is a rock star!&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;Great speaker.&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;Great - bring him back next year!&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;Awesome!&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;Fabulous session!!!&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;The Canadian presenters are in the lead on many topics.&rdquo;<br />\r\n&ldquo;He&rsquo;s very good at simplifying the economics.&rdquo; </em></p>\r\n</div>',32),(64,'extended','','',32),(65,'session','Fckeditor','',6),(66,'session','Fckeditor','',2),(67,'session','Fckeditor','',22),(68,'session','Fckeditor','',21),(69,'session','Fckeditor','',11),(70,'session','Fckeditor','',23),(71,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=